{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FeassgdqxbdsRQAD2ttHvW","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information you requested. Here's the comprehensive summary:\n\n## 1. tests/run-scenarios.sh (Full Content)\n\nThe file is a comprehensive test runner for scenario fixtures. Key features:\n\n**Core Functions:**\n- `usage()` - Shows help with examples like `tests/run-scenarios.sh cargo-agent` or `tests/run-scenarios.sh npm-agent/issues`\n- `scenario_label_from_file()` - Extracts friendly names from scenario paths\n- `list_scenarios()` - Finds all `scenario.env` files in tests directory\n- `missing_required_tool()` - Checks if required tools are installed\n- `run_one()` - Executes a single scenario test\n\n**run_one() Workflow:**\n1. Sources the scenario.env file to load: `SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, `REQUIRED_TOOLS`\n2. Validates the agent script exists and is executable\n3. Skips if required tools are missing\n4. Changes to scenario directory\n5. Runs the agent script with `RUN_ARGS`\n6. Compares exit code to `EXPECT_EXIT`\n7. If failure, prints first 40 lines of log output with hint to check full log\n\n**Other features:**\n- `run_shellcheck()` - Validates all shell scripts in the project with `--severity=warning`\n- `main()` - Orchestrates everything, supports filtering by name and `--list` mode\n\n---\n\n## 2. Example scenario.env Files\n\n**cargo-agent/clean/scenario.env:**\n```\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"cargo-agent clean\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=\"0\"\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"cargo jq\"\n```\n\n**cargo-agent/issues/scenario.env:**\n```\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"cargo-agent issues\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=\"1\"\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"cargo jq\"\n```\n\n**npm-agent/clean/scenario.env:**\n```\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"npm-agent clean\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=\"0\"\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"node npm\"\n```\n\n**npm-agent/issues/scenario.env:**\n```\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"npm-agent issues\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=\"1\"\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"node npm\"\n```\n\nThe pattern is clear: clean scenarios expect exit code 0 (success), issues scenarios expect exit code 1 (failure). Both set `RUN_ARGS=\"all\"` to test the full workflow.\n\n---\n\n## 3. cargo-agent.sh Command Dispatch (lines 551-594)\n\n```bash\nmain() {\n  while [[ \"${1:-}\" == --* ]]; do\n    case \"$1\" in\n      --fail-fast) FAIL_FAST=1; shift ;;\n      *) break ;;\n    esac\n  done\n\n  local cmd=\"${1:-all}\"\n  shift 2>/dev/null || true\n  local overall_ok=1\n\n  resolve_affected_packages\n\n  case \"$cmd\" in\n    -h|--help|help) usage; exit 0 ;;\n    fmt)   run_fmt   || overall_ok=0 ;;\n    check) run_check || overall_ok=0 ;;\n    clippy) run_clippy || overall_ok=0 ;;\n    sqlx) run_sqlx_verify || overall_ok=0 ;;\n    test)  run_tests \"$@\" || overall_ok=0 ;;\n    all)\n      # sqlx runs early: it verifies the cache before compilation steps, and\n      # a stale cache causes confusing downstream errors in check/clippy.\n      if [[ \"$RUN_FMT\" == \"1\" ]] && should_continue; then run_fmt || overall_ok=0; fi\n      if [[ \"$RUN_SQLX\" == \"1\" ]] && should_continue; then run_sqlx_verify || overall_ok=0; fi\n      # Skip check when clippy is enabled — clippy is a superset of check.\n      if [[ \"$RUN_CHECK\" == \"1\" && \"$RUN_CLIPPY\" != \"1\" ]] && should_continue; then run_check || overall_ok=0; fi\n      if [[ \"$RUN_CLIPPY\" == \"1\" ]] && should_continue; then run_clippy || overall_ok=0; fi\n      if [[ \"$RUN_TESTS\" == \"1\" ]] && should_continue; then run_tests || overall_ok=0; fi\n      ;;\n    *)\n      echo \"Unknown command: $cmd\" >&2\n      usage\n      exit 2\n      ;;\n  esac\n\n  print_overall \"$overall_ok\"\n  [[ \"$overall_ok\" == \"1\" ]]\n}\n\nmain \"$@\"\n```\n\n**Dispatch Strategy:**\n- First parses global flags like `--fail-fast`\n- Defaults to `all` if no command provided\n- Single commands (fmt, check, clippy, sqlx, test) run independently\n- `all` mode chains steps with `should_continue()` gate and respects `RUN_*` environment knobs\n- Unknown commands print usage and exit with code 2"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a054f8a720a574c44 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 26538\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 18077</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c026452d-4e68-40df-a262-fb1f2cd29fde","uuid":"764e79bb-6b25-4a41-b84f-dfecc7a08d87","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand:\n1. How tests/run-scenarios.sh works - read it fully\n2. An example clean scenario.env and issues scenario.env (from cargo-agent or npm-agent)\n3. How cargo-agent.sh handles command dispatch (the main/case block near the bottom of the file) - read skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh from line 80 onwards\n\nReturn the full content of run-scenarios.sh, example scenario.env files, and the command dispatch section of cargo-agent.sh.","agentId":"a054f8a720a574c44","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information you requested. Here's the comprehensive summary:\n\n## 1. tests/run-scenarios.sh (Full Content)\n\nThe file is a comprehensive test runner for scenario fixtures. Key features:\n\n**Core Functions:**\n- `usage()` - Shows help with examples like `tests/run-scenarios.sh cargo-agent` or `tests/run-scenarios.sh npm-agent/issues`\n- `scenario_label_from_file()` - Extracts friendly names from scenario paths\n- `list_scenarios()` - Finds all `scenario.env` files in tests directory\n- `missing_required_tool()` - Checks if required tools are installed\n- `run_one()` - Executes a single scenario test\n\n**run_one() Workflow:**\n1. Sources the scenario.env file to load: `SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `