{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0142dGbW77J5kuXhyxJ6S6ve","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# x-agent Exploration Notes\n     2→\n     3→## Key Files & Roles\n     4→\n     5→- `lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared boilerplate for x-agent runners. Provides output helpers, tool validation, output directory/cleanup setup, workflow locking, and summary output helpers. Sourced by every runnable agent script.\n     6→- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: Rust workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains run_x step handlers and domain-specific helpers (jq diagnostics, package resolution, nextest).\n     7→- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: Node workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains package-manager detection and file-scoping logic for lint/format.\n     8→- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: Terraform workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains safe init/plan behavior and optional tflint checks.\n     9→- `skills/bash-agent/scripts/bash-agent.sh`: planned Bash/Shell agent using shared library for syntax checking (`bash -n`) and shellcheck lint.\n    10→- `skills/bash-agent/SKILL.md`: planned trigger metadata and allowed tool declarations for shell script checks.\n    11→- `tests/run-scenarios.sh`: single orchestrator for shellcheck and fixture execution, including optional filtering by agent/scenario fragment.\n    12→- `tests/bash-agent/`: new clean/issues fixture set for FR-13 implementation.\n    13→- `tests/*/scenario.env`: declares `SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, and `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.\n    14→- `tests/cargo-agent/flock/flock-test.sh`: validates lock wait behavior using a competing holder process and waiting-message assertions.\n    15→- `install.sh`: installs skills, patches paths, and now includes `lib/x-agent-common.sh` for both local/remote install modes.\n    16→- `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`: canonical structure guide for script boilerplate, helpers, output contract, and agent metadata.\n    17→- `docs/agents/scenario-tests.md` and `docs/testing.md`: fixture contracts and local/CI test flow.\n    18→- `docs/agents/definition-of-done.md`: acceptance checks for output contract, env knobs, and scenario fixtures.\n    19→- `AGENTS.md`: root conventions for Bash 3.2 compatibility, structured output contract, and failure/skip semantics.\n    20→- `.github/workflows/ci.yml`: CI entrypoint that runs `tests/run-scenarios.sh` per agent and optional tool-matrix variants.\n    21→\n    22→## Patterns & Conventions\n    23→\n    24→- Script header pattern: `#!/usr/bin/env bash` + `set -euo pipefail`.\n    25→- Output format is strict and machine-compatible: each step prints `Step:`, `Result: PASS|FAIL|SKIP`, optional `Fix:`, and `Time:`; run end prints `Overall:` and `Logs:`.\n    26→- Runtime knobs are env-overridable: `RUN_<STEP>`, `KEEP_DIR`, `MAX_LINES`, `FAIL_FAST`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`, `CHANGED_FILES`.\n    27→- `FAIL_FAST` uses guarded dispatch: evaluate `should_continue()` before each run step when running `all`.\n    28→- Temp logs flow through `$OUTDIR`; failures and keep-mode preserve temp directory with `Logs kept in: <path>` from trap; success normally removes temp dir.\n    29→- Concurrent invocations are serialized by lockfiles (`${TMPDIR_ROOT}/<agent>.lock`) using `flock` with Perl fallback.\n    30→- `CI` detection switches behavior for line truncation and format checks: CI defaults to `MAX_LINES=999999` and check-only modes where applicable.\n    31→- Optional tools use skip/fallback behavior rather than hard failure; required tools must trigger `exit 2`.\n    32→- Bash compatibility baseline is 3.2: no associative arrays, no `readarray`, no `|&`, no associative case fallthrough.\n    33→- New agents should support `--help`/`help`/`-h` before any project-existence checks and reuse `setup_outdir` + `setup_lock` from `lib/x-agent-common.sh`.\n    34→\n    35→## Database Schema\n    36→\n    37→No database is used.\n    38→\n    39→## Test Infrastructure\n    40→\n    41→- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` discovers all `tests/*/scenario.env` fixtures, runs `shellcheck` first (or if filtered), and executes each scenario in fixture directories.\n    42→- Fixture runner expects relative script path via `AGENT_SCRIPT`; missing script prints `SKIP`.\n    43→- If a declared `REQUIRED_TOOLS` item is unavailable, the scenario is `SKIP`.\n    44→- `EXPECT_EXIT` values are asserted; mismatch prints log + first 40 lines.\n    45→- `tests/cargo-agent/flock` adds explicit lock contention coverage; scenario uses `help` mode to keep run short while validating wait message and eventual completion.\n    46→- `tests/run-scenarios.sh --list` enumerates full fixture labels (`tests/<agent>/<case>`), useful to target validation slices.\n    47→- CI runs the same command (`tests/run-scenarios.sh <filter>`) and adds optional matrix variants for `nextest` and `tflint`.\n    48→\n    49→## Architecture & Data Flow\n    50→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c026452d-4e68-40df-a262-fb1f2cd29fde","uuid":"6a9d2f8e-cdc3-49d2-9a9b-f6ec25f06b70","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/exploration.md","content":"# x-agent Exploration Notes\n\n## Key Files & Roles\n\n- `lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared boilerplate for x-agent runners. Provides output helpers, tool validation, output directory/cleanup setup, workflow locking, and summary output helpers. Sourced by every runnable agent script.\n- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: Rust workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains run_x step handlers and domain-specific helpers (jq diagnostics, package resolution, nextest).\n- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: Node workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains package-manager detection and file-scoping logic for lint/format.\n- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: Terraform workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains safe init/plan behavior and optional tflint checks.\n- `skills/bash-agent/scripts/bash-agent.sh`: planned Bash/Shell agent using shared library for syntax checking (`bash -n`) and shellcheck lint.\n- `skills/bash-agent/SKILL.md`: planned trigger metadata and allowed tool declarations for shell script checks.\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh`: single orchestrator for shellcheck and fixture execution, including optional filtering by agent/scenario fragment.\n- `tests/bash-agent/`: new clean/issues fixture set for FR-13 implementation.\n- `tests/*/scenario.env`: declares `SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, and `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.\n- `tests/cargo-agent/flock/flock-test.sh`: validates lock wait behavior using a competing holder process and waiting-message assertions.\n- `install.sh`: installs skills, patches paths, and now includes `lib/x-agent-common.sh` for both local/remote install modes.\n- `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`: canonical structure guide for script boilerplate, helpers, output contract, and agent metadata.\n- `docs/agents/scenario-tests.md` and `docs/testing.md`: fixture contracts and local/CI test flow.\n- `docs/agents/definition-of-done.md`: acceptance checks for output contract, env knobs, and scenario fixtures.\n- `AGENTS.md`: root conventions for Bash 3.2 compatibility, structured output contract, and failure/skip semantics.\n- `.github/workflows/ci.yml`: CI entrypoint that runs `tests/run-scenarios.sh` per agent and optional tool-matrix variants.\n\n## Patterns & Conventions\n\n- Script header pattern: `#!/usr/bin/env bash` + `set -euo pipefail`.\n- Output format is strict and machine-compatible: each step prints `Step:`, `Result: PASS|FAIL|SKIP`, optional `Fix:`, and `Time:`; run end prints `Overall:` and `Logs:`.\n- Runtime knobs are env-overridable: `RUN_<STEP>`, `KEEP_DIR`, `MAX_LINES`, `FAIL_FAST`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`, `CHANGED_FILES`.\n- `FAIL_FAST` uses guarded dispatch: evaluate `should_continue()` before each run step when running `all`.\n- Temp logs flow through `$OUTDIR`; failures and keep-mode preserve temp directory with `Logs kept in: <path>` from trap; success normally removes temp dir.\n- Concurrent invocations are serialized by lockfiles (`${TMPDIR_ROOT}/<agent>.lock`) using `flock` with Perl fallback.\n- `CI` detection switches behavior for line truncation and format checks: CI defaults to `MAX_LINES=999999` and check-only modes where applicable.\n- Optional tools use skip/fallback behavior rather than hard failure; required tools must trigger `exit 2`.\n- Bash compatibility baseline is 3.2: no associative arrays, no `readarray`, no `|&`, no associative case fallthrough.\n- New agents should support `--help`/`help`/`-h` before any project-existence checks and reuse `setup_outdir` + `setup_lock` from `lib/x-agent-common.sh`.\n\n## Database Schema\n\nNo database is used.\n\n## Test Infrastructure\n\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` discovers all `tests/*/scenario.env` fixtures, runs `shellcheck` first (or if filtered), and executes each scenario in fixture directories.\n- Fixture runner expects relative script path via `AGENT_SCRIPT`; missing script prints `SKIP`.\n- If a declared `REQUIRED_TOOLS` item is unavailable, the scenario is `SKIP`.\n- `EXPECT_EXIT` values are asserted; mismatch prints log + first 40 lines.\n- `tests/cargo-agent/flock` adds explicit lock contention coverage; scenario uses `help` mode to keep run short while validating wait message and eventual completion.\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh --list` enumerates full fixture labels (`tests/<agent>/<case>`), useful to target validation slices.\n- CI runs the same command (`tests/run-scenarios.sh <filter>`) and adds optional matrix variants for `nextest` and `tflint`.\n\n## Architecture & Data Flow\n","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":57}}}
