 (SC2034) and unset-variable (SC2154) which are genuine warnings.\n- **Modified `tests/run-scenarios.sh`**: Added `-not -path '*/issues/*'` to the shellcheck find command to exclude issue fixture scripts from the project-wide shellcheck scan. Without this, intentionally-bad fixtures in `tests/bash-agent/issues/` would fail the global shellcheck step.\n\n## Edge cases handled\n- `CHANGED_FILES` filtering: only existing `.sh` files are included\n- No `.sh` files discovered: prints `Result: SKIP (no matching .sh files)` and returns 0\n- Help/--help/-h: handled before `need` checks so it works without shellcheck installed\n- Unknown commands: print usage and exit 2\n- Shellcheck wiki links: extracts unique SC codes from output, limits to first 5, builds wiki URLs\n- `SHELLCHECK_SEVERITY` override: passes through to shellcheck `--severity` flag\n- `FAIL_FAST`: uses `should_continue()` from shared lib in `all` command path\n\n## Tests written/run\n- `tests/bash-agent/clean/` — passes with exit 0 (valid script, all checks pass)\n- `tests/bash-agent/issues/` — fails with exit 1 (shellcheck warnings in bad.sh)\n- `shellcheck --severity=warning` passes on bash-agent.sh itself\n- Full suite: all 14 scenarios pass (including all existing agents)\n\n## Known limitations\n- `bash -n` only checks syntax, not runtime errors — this is by design\n- File discovery splits `CHANGED_FILES` on whitespace, so paths with spaces are not supported (matches convention used by all other agents)\n- `shellcheck` is invoked once with all files as arguments; very large file lists could hit argument length limits (unlikely in practice)\n\n## Exploration notes\nUpdated `.ralph/exploration.md`: changed bash-agent entries from \"planned\" to implemented descriptions, noted the `run-scenarios.sh` exclusion of issue fixtures from shellcheck, and documented the fixture contents.\n\n## Lessons Applied This Phase\nNo prior lessons existed for this project. No new lessons required — implementation followed established patterns cleanly.\n\n## Suggestions for the REVIEW agent\n- Verify `--help` works without shellcheck installed (it should since help is parsed before `need` calls)\n- The `run-scenarios.sh` change to exclude `*/issues/*` from shellcheck is important for all future agents with intentionally-bad shell fixtures\n- `print_result` from shared lib is used by bash-agent (first agent to adopt it) — validates the shared lib API\n- Consider whether future agents also need the `*/issues/*` shellcheck exclusion documented in contributing docs\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
